-- Romania’s State-Firms Must Cede 85% of Profit, Mediafax Says
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2011-12-28T07:49:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/romania-s-state-firms-must-cede-85-of-profit-mediafax-says.html
Romania ’s state-owned companies must
transfer 85 percent of their profits to the state budget next
year,  Mediafax  reported today, citing Finance Minister Gheorghe Ialomitianu.  The country’s government approved a memorandum that lowered
the percentage from the profit of state-owned firms which must
be transferred to the state budget from the current 90 percent,
according to the Bucharest-based news service.  Romania will not increase taxes in 2012, Ialomitianu also
said, according to Mediafax.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  